üîπ Escape Character ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§π‡•à?

Escape character ‡§µ‡•ã special character ‡§π‡•à ‡§ú‡•ã string ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•ã‡§à special ‡§ï‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è use ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§
Python ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ø‡•á ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§∂‡§æ backslash \ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∂‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ç ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§

# Python Escape Characters Notes - Detailed Version

# -------------------------------------------
# 1. What is Escape Character?
# Escape character ‡§è‡§ï special character ‡§π‡•à ‡§ú‡•ã string ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç special ‡§ï‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à
# Python ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç escape character ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§∂‡§æ backslash \ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∂‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ç ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à
# ‡§á‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ use string ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§¶‡§∞ special symbol ‡§Ø‡§æ formatting ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à
# Example:
b = "Hello\nWorld"  # \n = new line
print(b)  # Output: 
# Hello
# World

# -------------------------------------------
# 2. Common Escape Characters

# \n ‚Üí New line
print("Line1\nLine2")  # Output:
# Line1
# Line2

# \t ‚Üí Tab space (extra gap)
print("Name:\tNishant")  # Output: Name:    Nishant

# \\ ‚Üí Backslash
print("C:\\Users\\Nishant")  # Output: C:\Users\Nishant

# \' ‚Üí Single quote
print("It\'s my book")  # Output: It's my book

# \" ‚Üí Double quote
print("He said, \"Hi\"")  # Output: He said, "Hi"

# -------------------------------------------
# 3. Important Points

# 1. Escape character ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§∂‡§æ backslash \ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∂‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ç ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à
# 2. Python string ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç slicing ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç start index included ‡§î‡§∞ end index excluded ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à
# 3. Windows path ‡§≤‡§ø‡§ñ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è \\ ‡§Ø‡§æ raw string r"" use ‡§ï‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç
# 4. Invalid escape sequence (\P, \Q) Python error ‡§¶‡•á‡§ó‡§æ
# 5. \n = new line, \t = tab, \\ = backslash, \' = single quote, \" = double quote

# -------------------------------------------
# 4. Quick Trick to Remember

# Formula: \ + special symbol = special action
# Examples:
# \n = new line
# \t = tab space
# \\ = backslash
# \' = single quote
# \" = double quote

# -------------------------------------------
# 5. Output Examples

print("Hello\nWorld")        # Output:
# Hello
# World

print("Name:\tNishant")      # Output: Name:    Nishant

print("C:\\Users\\Nishant")  # Output: C:\Users\Nishant

print("It\'s my book")       # Output: It's my book

print("He said, \"Hi\"")     # Output: He said, "Hi"

# -------------------------------------------
# 6. Extra Tip

# Double backslash \\ ‚Üí actual backslash print ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è
# Raw string r" " ‚Üí special characters ignore ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è
print(r"C:\Users\Nishant")  # Output: C:\Users\Nishant
